sdp/logs/Verify_T-032_20260427T001208Zb_1777273461.log:130:{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:05:50.265Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777273549882_0","status":"success","output":"Rows: 8\n5:- Added a steady-state SDP cost extractor and committed CSV (T-032@b): `promptclaw/sdp_cost.py` exposes `TOKEN_PRICING`, `match_pricing`, `call_cost_usd`, `DailyCostRow`, `extract_steady_state_cost`, and `write_csv`, applying the substring-matched pricing table from `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md` (claude-opus-4 $15/$75, claude-sonnet-4 $3/$15, claude-haiku $0.80/$4, gpt-4o $2.50/$10, o3 $10/$40, codex-mini $1.50/$6, fallback $3/$15) to per-task `lead_profile_id` rows in the `.sdp/state.db` `telemetry` table. The CLI `python -m promptclaw.sdp_cost --db .sdp/state.db --days 7 --out sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` rolls the 7 most recent active UTC days into the committed `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` (header `date,runs,input_tokens,output_tokens,cache_creation_tokens,cache_read_tokens,total_cost_usd,models`); `cache_creation_tokens`, `cache_read_tokens`, and `thinking_tokens` are reported but not billed, matching the cost-model.md formula. Test coverage in `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` pins the pricing table values, substring-and-fallback matching, the cost-model.md worked example (`(in/1e6*in_p)+(out/1e6*out_p)`), per-day grouping with sorted unique tier lists, the locked CSV header schema with 4-decimal USD formatting and `|`-joined models, and the CLI's stdout path echo."}
sdp/logs/Verify_T-032_20260427T001208Zb_1777273461.log:150:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-27T07:06:12.072Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777273572071_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-032@20260427t001208zb-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-032@20260427T001208Zb\n\n**Verify Agent:** gemini\n**Date:** 2026-04-27\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `promptclaw/sdp_cost.py`\n- `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv`\n- `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py`\n- `CHANGELOG.md`\n- `specs/t-032@20260427t001208zb-spec.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `promptclaw/sdp_cost.py` correctly fulfills all requirements of the specification:\n- `TOKEN_PRICING` table matches the cost-model documentation verbatim.\n- `match_pricing` implements case-insensitive substring matching with a fallback tier.\n- `call_cost_usd` applies the correct formula `(in/1e6 * in_p) + (out/1e6 * out_p)`.\n- `extract_steady_state_cost` correctly aggregates telemetry data by UTC date for the requested number of active days.\n- `write_csv` produces a stable schema with 4-decimal USD formatting and `|`-joined models.\n- The CLI wrapper correctly handles `--db`, `--days`, and `--out` arguments.\n\nThe committed `sdp/telemetry/steady-state-cost.csv` contains 7 active days of data as required.\n\n## Completeness\nAll items in the Technical Approach and Acceptance Criteria have been addressed. The extractor correctly handles edge cases like empty `lead_profile_id`, zero token counts, and reporting non-billed token types (cache/thinking tokens).\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows established patterns in the repository. The use of `dataclasses`, `sqlite3`, and `argparse` is consistent with other modules. The test file `tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` follows existing testing conventions.\n\n## Security\nNo security issues were identified. Database access is read-only for extraction. CSV writing uses the standard `csv` module which handles escaping. No secrets or credentials are involved or exposed.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-documented with docstrings and comments explaining the pricing logic. Tests provide comprehensive coverage of all core functions and the CLI. `CHANGELOG.md` has been updated with detailed notes.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No blocking issues found.\n- [ ] (Note) Full test suite `pytest tests/ -x` fails due to pre-existing macOS Seatbelt restrictions on daemon tests that attempt to write to `~/.promptclaw/pets.json`. This is unrelated to T-032. Dedicated tests for this task (`tests/test_sdp_cost_extractor.py` and `tests/test_sdp_telemetry_cost_model.py`) pass 100%.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and the resulting report provides exactly the visibility requested. The decision to interpret \"7+ consecutive days\" as \"7 most recent active days\" was correct given the calendar gaps in the telemetry data.\n"}}
