CHANGELOG.md:53:- Added depth-2 startle daemon processing (frac-0034): `my-claw/tools/startle_daemon.py` is now import-safe and exposes typed helpers `read_room_activity`, `amp_from_room`, `update_baseline`, `baseline_value`, `render_output`, `write_output`, `process_once`, and `run_daemon` plus a `DaemonState` dataclass that combines the existing `senseweave.startle.StartleState` with a rolling-baseline tracker. The daemon now reads `/tmp/room_activity.json`, takes the louder of `window_mic_amp` / `cypherclaw_mic_amp`, maintains a 20-sample rolling-median baseline (with a non-zero floor so the detector never sees a degenerate baseline), runs the existing `update_startle` rules, and atomically writes the consumer contract (`startled`, `startle_count`, `cooldown_active`, `face_reaction`, `should_mute`, `amp`, `baseline`, `timestamp`) consumed by `inner_life.world_model.poll_state`. Loop control gains `--once`, `--interval`, `--room-path`, `--state-path`, and `--max-iterations`; existing `senseweave.startle` rules are unchanged. `tests/test_startle_daemon.py` pins import safety, baseline/amp helpers, end-to-end loud-room startle output, and quiet-room loop output; `tests/test_startle.py` and the startup identity anchors remain regression coverage.
